    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - ENGINE ELECTRICAL - Description of Engine Sensors and Valves -
        Camshaft Position (CMP) Sensor
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26510.2.2" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Camshaft Position (CMP) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f2651005" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd09/D0947.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>CMP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The CMP sensor, a magnetic pickup sensor, indicates camshaft speed and position.</para>
        <para>The CMP sensor sends a pulsed signal to the ECM when a single peg on the camshaft rotates past the CMP
            sensor once during each revolution of the camshaft. The ECM calculates camshaft speed and position from CMP
            signal frequency.
        </para>
        <para>The CMP sensor is installed in the front left side of the crankcase.</para>
    </svcproc>
